"{\"uid\": \"myrepublica.nagariknetwork.com-news-paris-olympics-2024-prince-dahal-loses-to-danish-badminton-player\", \"text\": \"Subscribe Now  KATHMANDU, July 28: Badminton player Prince Dahal has lost to Victor Axelsen of Denmark in the Paris Olympics. Dahal lost in straight sets 2-0 in the match held last night at Porte De La Chapelle Arena in Paris, France.  Prince lost the match to Victor in straight sets of 21-8 and 21-6 Prince will now play against Ireland's Hat Nguyen on Monday and on July 30 he will play against Israel's Misa Zilberman.  Nepal has been participating in the Olympics since the 1964 Tokyo Olympics. This is the first time that a Nepali athlete is competing in badminton in the Olympics.  Later today, Sushmita Nepal from Nepal will compete in 10m air rifle shooting while Duwana Lama will compete in 200m freestyle swimming.  Ballot Box Revolt: What RSP's breakthrough victory...  Warning, Threat or Opportunity? Nepal's major part...  Granary in crisis: Water politics leave Madhesh pa...  \\\"China stands ready to work with Nepal to carry forward the traditional friendship, deepen practical cooperation and advance bilateral relations\\\", read the statement.  Building Nepal's Digital Future  Fuel shortages in Nepal: A hidden threat to health a...  Second Innings of Balen and Gagan  Who will become Balen's climate pilot?  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  Three \\\"S\\\" factors-sulabhata (availability), sangat (peer influence), and siko (imitation)-are driving Madhesh's youth toward drug addiction.<...  ANFA CEO Indraman Tuladhar said the ANFA submitted all necessary documents regarding foreign players' visas to the Ministry of Youth and Sports and the National Sports Council one and a half mon...  Nepal Republic Media Limited \\u00a9 2026.All right reserved  Nepal Republic Media Limited \\u00a9 2024. All right reserved |Privacy Pol